==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Id
<hw>Id</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A small
fresh-water cyprinoid fish (<spn>Leuciscus idus</spn> or <spn>Idus
idus</spn>) of Europe. A domesticated variety, colored like the
goldfish, is called <altname>orfe</altname> in Germany.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>id</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: id
<hw>id</hw> <pr>(⟦icr⟧d)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Psychoanalysis)</fld>
<def>That part of a person's psyche which is the unconscious source of
impulses seeking gratification or pleasure; the impulses are usually
modified by the <contr>ego</contr> and <contr>superego</contr> before
being acted upon.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Idahoan</ent>⟦br⟧
